        <h1>Why "Hollow Log"?</h1>
        <p>Hollow logs were used as early American water, sewer, and fire systems. As of 2009, Chelan, WA had over 500 feet of hollow log pipe still in use, as well as unused wood water pipe on display in their public works office.</p>
        <p>Having worked on very old homes and buildings in the Seattle area for over 30 years, we grew to admire and respect the generations of plumbers who invented, designed, and built these systems. Hollow Log Plumbing is simply a nod of appreciation to the generations of plumbers that came before us.</p>
