        <h1>Our Story</h1>
        <p>Mark Schlieps began plumbing at age 19 in the non-union sector, doing a wide variety of residential and commercial work. After 5 years he opened Plumb-Rite in 1988, specializing in residential remodels, repipes, and commercial restaurants such as Red Robin and Azteca.</p> 
        <p>After 11 successful years of business, Mark joined UA Local 32 Plumbers and Pipefitters. He cultivated 17 years of his career in the union working in the core of downtown Seattle and Bellevue, repiping occupied apartments and commercial buildings.</p> 
        <p>Now, with over 35 years of experience, Mark owns and operates Hollow Log Plumbing and has returned to his roots in residential remodels and commercial tenant improvements.</p>
